  <li id="comment-43798" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/17016541751604349458" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Michele Unger</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/01/we-adopted-the-habit/#comment-43798"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-01-25T17:37:54-05:00">Sunday, January 25, 2015 at 5:37 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m I spent an incredible week in Oaxaca City last fall at an art retreat and had a glorious time, too.  I can&#39;t say enough about the food! The moles were astoundingly good and Oaxaca is known for seven different types.  I tried them all and I would be hard pressed to pick a favorite.  Oaxaca was as memorable to me as your holiday was for you and your friends.  </p>
<p>Did you try grilled octopus?  OMG&#8230; I dream about grilled octopus now!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
