      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/01/we-adopted-the-habit/#comment-43801"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-01-31T05:48:54-05:00">Saturday, January 31, 2015 at 5:48 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Your writer&#39;s voice is so enviably clear and compelling, that  even though I am in the midst of a year of traveling with my family to all  sorts of great places I am suddenly wishing we had Oaxaca on our itinerary&#8230;</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-43801' data-commentid="43801" data-postid="41" data-belowelement="comment-43801" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-43802" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/01/we-adopted-the-habit/#comment-43802"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-02-03T18:07:18-05:00">Tuesday, February 3, 2015 at 6:07 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>It was wonderful reading about the land where many of my dear friends call home and hope to return to someday. They are the people who work in the fields picking most of the fruits and vegetables we eat.  They remain in the shadows, for the most part, almost invisible and held of little account.<br />And yet, the food of these gracious and humble people is nothing short of maravilloso&#8211;a delicious alchemy of the cuisines of the Old and New Worlds.  How I wish you had been invited for lunch or dinner to the home of a Oaxacan abuelita (grandma), Molly. What hospitality and warmth you would have found in her tiny cocina! What an unforgettable meal you would have had! It is only in their cocinas where you will find the magnificence of a cuisine of, and for, the ages, prepared by the hands of a master, something no restaurant meal can ever duplicate.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-43802' data-commentid="43802" data-postid="41" data-belowelement="comment-43802" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
